    "attributes": {
        "action": "Reintroduce Feed-in Tariffs for domestic solar panels",
        "additional_details": "There are millions of roofs across the country that could be reducing England's carbon footprint and making us less vulnerable to bill increases from energy providers. The Government can help achieve this by reinstating financial incentives for installing renewable technology.",
        "background": "Help private households reduce their bills and promote the uptake of renewable energy by reopening the Feed-in Tariffs scheme to new applicants, so households can sell surplus energy back to the grid through a Government scheme.",
